The EFF's Julius Malema and Mbuyiseni Ndlozi return to court today. They are accused of assaulting a police officer Lieutenant-Colonel Johannes Venter.  Editor's note: This Livestream has ended. You may watch the recording above. #DStv403 #eNCA JOHANNESBURG - EFF leader Julius Malema and MP Mbuyiseni Ndlozi are back in court. They're facing assault charges over an incident dating back to April 2018 during the funeral of struggle stalwart, Winnie Madikizela-Mandela. WATCH: Malema, Ndlozi return to court CCTV footage of the incident was part of Tuesday’s testimony in the Randburg magistrate’s court.